Section 11.2 #14.
Find the limit, if it exists, or show that the limit does not exist.
\lim_{(x,y)\to(0,0)}\frac{xy^4}{x^2+y^8}

Section 11.3 #82. The wind-chill index is modeled by the function
W=13.12+0.6215T-11.37v^{0.16}+0.3965Tv^{0.16}
where T is the temperature (in Celsius) and v is the wind speed (in km/h). When T=-15 and v=30, by how much would you expect the apparent temperature W to drop if the actual temperature decreases by 1^{\circ}\mathrm{C}? What if the wind speed increases by 1 km/h?
